    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "DATA ANALYTICS MANAGER\n\nRiveron is seeking a seasoned Data Analytics Manager to lead our growing analytics team in India. This role is perfect for a strategic thinker with deep expertise in data analytics and leadership experience, who can drive data-driven decision-making and deliver actionable insights using advanced tools and technologies. If you’re passionate about analytics, business intelligence, and enabling data-driven strategies, we’d love to connect with you.\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE:\n\n - A data analytics professional with 8–10 years of experience, including 3+ years in a leadership or managerial role.\n\n - Strong foundation in data analytics, business intelligence, and visualization tools (Power BI, Tableau, or equivalent).\n\n - Proficient in SQL for complex query writing, data extraction, and performance optimization.\n\n - Skilled in Python or R for advanced analytics, automation, and statistical modeling.\n\n - Experienced in data modeling (relational, dimensional, and analytical models).\n\n - Familiar with cloud platforms (Azure preferred) and services like Azure Synapse Analytics, Azure Data Lake, Azure Databricks, and Microsoft Fabric.\n\n - Knowledgeable in ETL processes, data governance, and best practices for data quality and security.\n\n - Strong understanding of version control tools (Git) and collaborative development workflows.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO:\n\n - Lead and mentor a team of data analysts and engineers to deliver high-quality analytics solutions.\n\n - Design and implement data analytics strategies aligned with business objectives.\n\n - Oversee development of dashboards, reports, and predictive models to support decision-making.\n\n - Collaborate with stakeholders to define KPIs, metrics, and data requirements.\n\n - Ensure data accuracy, consistency, and compliance across all analytics initiatives.\n\n - Drive performance optimization for analytics workflows and reporting systems.\n\n - Champion best practices in data governance, security, and documentation.\n\n - Stay updated with emerging trends in analytics, AI/ML, and cloud technologies.\n\n\nPREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:\n\n - Hands-on experience with Azure Synapse Analytics, Power BI, Microsoft Fabric, and Azure SQL Database.\n\n - Familiarity with CI/CD pipelines and DevOps practices for analytics deployments.\n\n - Experience in Agile environments, including sprint planning and stakeholder reviews.\n\n - Strong business acumen and ability to translate data insights into actionable strategies.\n\n - Excellent communication and leadership skills to manage cross-functional teams.\n\nAbout Riveron:\n\nAt Riveron, we partner with clients—from global multinationals to high-growth private entities—to solve complex finance challenges, guided by our DELTA values: Drive, Excellence, Leadership, Teamwork, and Accountability. Our entrepreneurial culture thrives on collaboration, diverse perspectives, and delivering exceptional outcomes. We are committed to fostering growth, both for our clients and our people, through mentorship, integrity, and a client-centric approach. This inclusive environment offers flexibility, progressive benefits, and meaningful opportunities for impactful work that supports well-being in and out of the office.\n\nCheck us out on social media:\n\nLinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/riveron/life/culture/ Glassdoor https://www.glassdoor.com/Photos/Riveron-Office-Photos-E672242.htm Instagram https://www.instagram.com/riveronconsulting/ Facebook https://www.facebook.com/RiveronConsulting/\n\nRiveron Consulting is an Equal Opportunity Employer and believes that we are stronger together through our diversity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, sexual orientation, gender identity or any other characteristic protected by law.\n\nFull time roles are eligible for a full range of benefits including medical, dental, and vision insurance, 401(k) with company match, and PTO. A complete description of all available benefits can be found at Riveron's Benefits page at https://riveron.com/riveron-life/. Contract roles are not eligible for benefits.\n\n\nFRAUD ALERT\n\nPlease beware of fraudulent schemes or impersonations when going through the job application process. A Riveron employee will never recruit via text or extend unsolicited employment offers. Additionally, a Riveron employee will never ask you to exchange money or purchase anything as part of the recruiting process.\n\n\nWE MAY USE ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) TOOLS TO SUPPORT PARTS OF THE HIRING PROCESS, SUCH AS REVIEWING APPLICATIONS, ANALYZING RESUMES, OR ASSESSING RESPONSES. THESE TOOLS ASSIST OUR RECRUITMENT TEAM BUT DO NOT REPLACE HUMAN JUDGMENT. FINAL HIRING DECISIONS ARE ULTIMATELY MADE BY HUMANS. IF YOU WOULD LIKE MORE INFORMATION ABOUT HOW YOUR DATA IS PROCESSED, PLEASE CONTACT US.",
